_Pu’al_ Future Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_pu’al_ future tense]] follows these conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular*                           |\<  | *Plural*                               |\< |
| *First-Person* | אֲזֻמַּן<br>_azuman_<br>I will be invited | \< | נְזֻמַּן<br>_nezuman_<br>We will be invited | \< |
| *Second-Person* |תְּזֻמַּן <br>_tezuman_<br> You [male] will be invited | תְּזֻמְּנִי <br>_tezumni_<br> You [female] will be invited  | תְּזֻמְּנוּ <br>_tezumnu_<br> You [males] will be invited  | תְּזֻמַּנָּה <br>_tezumannau_<br> You [females] will be invited  |
| *Third-Person* |יְזֻמַּן <br>_yezuman_<br> He will be invited | תְּזֻמַּן <br>_tezuman_<br> She will be invited  | יְזֻמְּנוּ <br>_yezumnu_<br> [Those males] will be invited  | תְּזֻמַּנָּה <br>_tezumannau_<br> [Those females] will be invited  |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ז, ‎מ, and ן above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
